      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">40.202-6</ph> Waivers.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <p class="- topic/p ">The head of the agency may waive the prohibitions under <xref href="40.202.dita#FAR_40_202"
                  outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                  class="- topic/xref ">40.202</xref> on a case-by-case basis in accordance with agency procedures and based on the statutory waiver provisions (sections 1823, 1824, and 1825 of Pub. L. 118-31, 41 U.S.C. 3901 note prec.)â€”</p>
         <ol class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d2458e12">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>With the approval of the Director of the Office of Management and Budget, after consultation with the FASC; and</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d2458e17">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>Upon notification to-</p>
               <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d2458e23">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph> The Committee on Homeland Security and Governmental Affairs of the Senate;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d2458e28">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> The Committee on Oversight and Accountability in the House of Representatives; and</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d2458e33">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph> Other appropriate congressional committees of jurisdiction.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
   </concept>
